<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920127-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>920127-0026.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- UCC Investors Holding Inc.:   Uniroyal Chemical to File   For Initial Public Offering</HL><DATE>01/27/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13</SO><CO>   X.UKS</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)SPECIALTY CHEMICALS (CHS)INITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><NS>INITIAL PUBLIC OFFERINGS (INI)BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Uniroyal Chemical Co. is joining the crowd of businessestaken private in the 1980s leveraged buy-out binge that areplanning to go public once again.   UCC Investors Holding Inc., Uniroyal Chemical's parent,said it plans to file this week registration statements forproposed offerings of $400 million in stock and $300 millionin senior notes. UCC said it plans to use the proceeds toretire debt.</LP><TEXT>   Uniroyal Chemical, a Middlebury, Conn., specialtychemicals concern, was purchased in 1989 from Avery Inc. in amanagement-led buy-out for $240 million in cash and theassumption of $560 million in debt.   UCC Investors said the initial public offering price isexpected to range from $14 million to $16 million a share. Itadded that the debt to be retired are its 14% senior discountnotes due 1999 at 110.9% of accreted value; 13.5% seniorsubordinated notes of its Uniroyal Chemical AcquisitionCorp., due 1997 at 109.64% of principal amount; and UCAC's14.25% subordinated notes due 1998 at 108.91% of principalamount.</TEXT></DOC>